This paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) category as it deals with the problem of Part of Speech tagging in the context of linguistic code switching. It also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which makes it relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper explores multiple strategies for processing code-switched data, which could be relevant to the Natural Language Processing (cs.NE) and Sound and Speech Processing (cs.SD) categories.
